                    <td width="540" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><p class="bdtxt">The  Umayal Play School and Day Care center is run by &ldquo;The Ashoka Charitable Trust&rdquo;,  was opened by the Justice Mr. S Mohan on 4th Oct 2002.<br />
                          <br />
                      Umayal  Play School is dedicated to fostering a social, emotional, cognitive, physical  and creative growth of the child. We follow and integrated learning curriculum  that encourages an overall development. The school provides a safe and secure  environment. Our program is grounded on the principles about the growth and  development of children. In order to facilitate self-directed learning UPS is  set up with a variety of stimulating materials and challenging activities for  children to choose from.<br />
                      <br />
                        Our  guiding principle for the playgroup program is to help your child master the  skills needed for an overall success. Our program introduces your children to a  more structure day with stimulating activities, group interaction and numerous  opportunities. Our curriculum and monthly themes are based on real world  sensory experiences. Your child will spend a major part of his day singing,  dancing laughing playing and exploring.<br />
                        <br />
                        The  monthly themes have been devised to help your child build cognitive, language,  motor and social skills and self-esteem.<br />
                        <br />
                        Our  nursery program teaches essential skills like sequence that encourages children  to learn one step at a time.<br />
                        <br />
                        Monthly  themes, weekly topics and daily activities keep the curriculum focused and  teach key academics skill to children. The activities encourage curiosity,  self-initiative and persistence.<br />
                        <br />
                        The  academic curriculum at Umayal Play School is &lsquo;the best&rsquo; part of educational  development of child with as much emphasis placed on preparation for the  future. We believe education is about for more than just academic success.</p>
